name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On August 11, the Hebei Provincial Government Information Office held a press conference on "Flood Control, Disaster Relief and Post-disaster Reconstruction in Hebei Province".
At the meeting, it was reported that from July 27 to August 2, affected by Typhoon Dusurui, Hebei Province suffered a rare heavy rainstorm and flood disaster in history. As of August 10, 29 people died in the province due to the disaster, including 6 people who were previously missing. Currently, 16 people are still missing, and rescue workers are still doing their best to search and rescue.
At the press conference, all personnel stood up and mourned for the victims.
